    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="631"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.85/12–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-09">December 9,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 9—11:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10946. To the Department and Land, WSA, for Morse from Reed and Allison. Foreign
                    Office has advised that Australia has indicated <pb facs="0744" n="734"
                        xml:id="pg_734"/> her desire to accede to Agreement on Principles by a note
                    which states they have also notified United States Government<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d631fn29">By note dated December 16, 1944, the Australian Legation
                        confirmed an informal notification made to the Department by telephone on
                        November 28.</note> they make no reservations according to UMEB paper
                        l.<note n="30" xml:id="d631fn30">Not printed; it contained the formal
                        procedure for accession of other governments given in the second paragraph
                        of the note of December 13 to the Brazilian Embassy, <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra</hi>.</note> If you agree we propose to notify other contracting
                    governments by letters signed by Weston and Brown that Australia is acceding
                    without reservation. Embassy will cable separately on form of notification to
                    Australia that her accession is accepted.<note n="31" xml:id="d631fn31">Telegram
                        10415, December 14, to London, stated that the Department and WSA agreed to
                        proposal and assumed that in due course formal protocol of accession would
                        be executed (103.9164 London).</note> [Reed and Allison.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
